{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Qa19FvxpNZbFsHfKp9FHkR","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Route & Auth Patterns Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`, here's the complete pattern you need to follow:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Application Setup & Route Registration** (`src/index.ts`)\n\n**Framework**: Hono (lightweight web framework)\n\n**Key Configuration**:\n```typescript\n// CORS enabled globally\napp.use(\"*\", cors({\n  origin: \"*\",\n  allowMethods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n  allowHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n}));\n\n// Request logging middleware (skips /health and OPTIONS)\napp.use(\"*\", async (c, next) => { /* timing + debug logging */ });\n```\n\n**Route Registration Pattern**:\n- Routes are registered via `app.route()` and `app.use()` to attach middleware\n- Auth routes mounted at `/auth` with lighter rate limiting (no JWT)\n- Fairness routes (`/fairness/*`) have both JWT middleware AND rate limiting applied\n- Health routes mounted at `/health`\n- Middleware is applied in order to specific path prefixes\n\n**Path Structure**:\n- `/auth/*` → Auth routes (challenge, verify, refresh, logout)\n- `/fairness/coinflip/*` → Coinflip routes\n- `/fairness/lord/*` → Lord of RNGs routes\n- `/closecall/*` → Close Call routes (different structure, not under /fairness)\n- `/fairness/rounds/*` → Round verification/history routes\n- `/health` → Health check\n\n---\n\n### 2. **JWT Auth Middleware** (`src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`)\n\n**How it works**:\n- Uses `jose` library for HS256 JWT verification\n- Verifies only on **POST requests** — GET requests pass through unauthenticated\n- Extracts JWT from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Stores wallet address in context: `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)`\n- Returns 401 for missing/invalid tokens\n\n**Key Points**:\n```typescript\n// JWT claim structure\npayload.sub === wallet address (base58 public key string)\n\n// Validation\n- Algorithm: HS256\n- Claim required: \"sub\" (must be string)\n- Returns: 401 on failure, 403 if JWT wallet doesn't match body wallet\n```\n\n**Applied Routes**:\n```typescript\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret }));\n// All POST requests under /fairness/* require a valid JWT\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Route Handler Pattern** (`src/routes/create.ts` and `src/routes/lord-create.ts`)\n\n**Function Signature**:\n```typescript\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // Handler code\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies Passed In**:\n- `db: Db` — database client\n- `connection: Connection` — Solana RPC connection\n- `serverKeypair: Keypair` — backend signing key\n- `pdaWatcher?: PdaWatcher` — optional WebSocket watcher for instant join detection\n\n**Hono Context Type**: `Hono<AppEnv>` where `AppEnv` defines `Variables: { wallet: string }`\n\n**Accessing Authenticated Wallet**:\n```typescript\nconst jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n// This is automatically set by JWT middleware for POST requests\n// For defense-in-depth, verify body.wallet matches jwtWallet\n```\n\n**Request/Response Pattern**:\n```typescript\n// Parse request\nconst raw = await c.req.json();\nconst body = validateBody(raw); // Custom validation function\n\n// Return JSON response\nreturn c.json({ key: value }, statusCode);\n\n// Error responses\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 400); // Bad request\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 401); // Unauthorized\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 403); // Forbidden\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 409); // Conflict\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 500); // Server error\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Database Patterns** (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Interface Structure**:\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>;\n  insertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getUserTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<UserTransaction[]>;\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string | null, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload?: unknown): Promise<OperatorEvent>;\n  // ... more methods\n}\n```\n\n**getUserTransactions Signature**:\n```typescript\nasync getUserTransactions(\n  wallet: string,\n  cursor?: string,    // Pagination cursor (id of last item)\n  limit?: number,     // Default 20, max 50\n  game?: string       // Optional game filter: \"coinflip\", \"lord\", \"closecall\"\n): Promise<UserTransaction[]>\n\n// Returns array of:\nexport interface UserTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  match_id: string;\n  event: \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  tx_sig: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- `insertUserTransaction` uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for idempotency\n- All amounts are stored in lamports (integers)\n- Database normalizes numeric types (number) on read\n- `cursor` is the `id` field for pagination (lexicographic ordering)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Common Route Handler Flow** (from `create.ts`)\n\n1. **Parse & Validate Request Body**\n   ```typescript\n   const raw = await c.req.json();\n   const body = validateBody(raw); // throws on invalid data\n   // Catch in try-catch, return 400 with error message\n   ```\n\n2. **Verify JWT Wallet Matches** (defense-in-depth)\n   ```typescript\n   const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n   if (jwtWallet && body.wallet !== jwtWallet) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Convert strings to PublicKey**\n   ```typescript\n   let creatorPubkey: PublicKey;\n   try {\n     creatorPubkey = new PublicKey(body.wallet);\n   } catch {\n     return c.json({ error: \"wallet is not a valid public key\" }, 400);\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Generate Game-Specific Data** (secrets, commitments, match IDs)\n   ```typescript\n   const secret = generateSecret(); // cryptographic random\n   const commitment = computeCommitment(secret); // SHA256 hash\n   const matchId = generateMatchId(); // 8-byte random buffer\n   ```\n\n5. **Derive PDA & Check for Duplicates**\n   ```typescript\n   const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creatorPubkey, matchId);\n   const matchPdaStr = matchPda.toBase58();\n   const existing = await db.getRoundByPda(matchPdaStr);\n   if (existing) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n   }\n   ```\n\n6. **Build & Sign Transaction**\n   ```typescript\n   try {\n     const result = await buildCreateMatchTx({ /* params */ });\n     transaction = result.transaction; // serialized, partial-signed\n     lastValidBlockHeight = result.lastValidBlockHeight;\n   } catch (err) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Failed to build transaction\" }, 500);\n   }\n   ```\n\n7. **Store in Database**\n   ```typescript\n   await db.insertRound({\n     pda: matchPdaStr,\n     game: \"coinflip\",\n     creator: body.wallet,\n     serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58(),\n     secret,\n     commitment,\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n     side: body.side,\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n     phase: \"created\",\n   });\n   ```\n\n8. **Insert User Transaction & Operator Events**\n   ```typescript\n   await db.insertUserTransaction({\n     wallet: body.wallet,\n     game: \"coinflip\",\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n     event: \"join\",\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n   });\n\n   await db.insertOperatorEvent(matchPdaStr, \"secret_generated\", {\n     creator: body.wallet,\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n     side: body.side,\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n   });\n   ```\n\n9. **Subscribe to PDA Watcher** (for instant join detection)\n   ```typescript\n   pdaWatcher?.watch(matchPdaStr);\n   ```\n\n10. **Return Response**\n    ```typescript\n    return c.json({\n      transaction,        // serialized txn string\n      matchPda: matchPdaStr,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      commitment: commitment.toString(\"hex\"),\n      lastValidBlockHeight,\n    });\n    ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Hono Context Type Definition** (`src/hono-env.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware\n  };\n};\n```\n\nAll route handlers should use `Hono<AppEnv>` to get proper type hints for `c.get(\"wallet\")`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **File Paths & Organization**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | App setup, middleware registration, route mounting |\n| `src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts` | JWT Bearer token verification |\n| `src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` | Per-wallet and global rate limiting |\n| `src/routes/*.ts` | Individual route handlers (exported as functions) |\n| `src/db.ts` | Database client factory + typed queries |\n| `src/hono-env.ts` | TypeScript context type augmentation |\n| `src/logger.js` | Structured logging (used for audit trails) |\n| `src/tx-builder.ts` | Transaction building utilities |\n| `src/fairness.js` | Commitment/secret generation |\n\n---\n\n### **Key Conventions for New Routes**\n\n1. **Export a factory function** that takes dependencies and returns a `Hono<AppEnv>` app\n2. **Use`app.post()` for operations that modify state** (game creation, joining, settlement)\n3. **Use `app.get()` for read-only queries** (round history, fairness data)\n4. **GET requests skip JWT auth automatically** — only POST requires Bearer token\n5. **Always validate request bodies** with a `validateBody()` function\n6. **Defense-in-depth**: verify `c.get(\"wallet\")` matches request body wallet\n7. **Use `c.json()` for all responses** — Hono handles serialization\n8. **Log at key points** (start, validation failure, DB error, success)\n9. **Database operations use sql template literals** with `postgres.js` client\n10. **Return camelCase in JSON responses** (e.g., `matchPda`, `amountLamports`), snake_case in DB\n\n---\n\n### **Routes Directory Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | HTTP Method | Path |\n|------|---------|-------------|------|\n| `auth.ts` | Sign-in flow | POST | `/auth/challenge`, `/auth/verify`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout` |\n| `create.ts` | Coinflip round creation | POST | `/fairness/coinflip/create` |\n| `lord-create.ts` | Lord of RNGs round creation | POST | `/fairness/lord/create`, GET `/fairness/lord/current` |\n| `closecall.ts` | Close Call (BTC prediction) | POST/GET | `/closecall/...` |\n| `rounds.ts` | Round verification & history | GET | `/fairness/rounds/history`, `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`, `/fairness/rounds/:pda` |\n| `health.ts` | System health | GET | `/health` |\n\nYou now have the complete pattern to write a new route that follows existing conventions exactly!"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a88b1d0e102ae1206 (use SendMessage with to: 'a88b1d0e102ae1206' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 59191\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 39966</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bdcb16e5-995f-4f3d-baa2-b8a7a74d44d2","uuid":"a3e2c0e8-ade8-427b-90d7-74e8d60d31d1","timestamp":"2026-03-19T18:54:53.379Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"I need to understand the backend route and auth patterns in `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/`. Specifically:\n\n1. Read `src/routes/` directory - list all files and read one or two representative route files to understand the pattern (router setup, auth middleware, request/response handling)\n2. Read how routes are registered in `src/index.ts` (or wherever the express/fastify app is configured)\n3. Find and read the JWT auth middleware - how is it applied to routes? How is the wallet extracted from the JWT?\n4. Read `src/db.ts` - specifically the `getUserTransactions` function signature and return type\n\nBe thorough - I need to write a new route that follows existing conventions exactly.","agentId":"a88b1d0e102ae1206","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have all the information needed. Let me compile a comprehensive report.\n\n## Backend Route & Auth Patterns Summary\n\nBased on my thorough exploration of `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/`, here's the complete pattern you need to follow:\n\n---\n\n### 1. **Application Setup & Route Registration** (`src/index.ts`)\n\n**Framework**: Hono (lightweight web framework)\n\n**Key Configuration**:\n```typescript\n// CORS enabled globally\napp.use(\"*\", cors({\n  origin: \"*\",\n  allowMethods: [\"GET\", \"POST\", \"OPTIONS\"],\n  allowHeaders: [\"Content-Type\", \"Authorization\"],\n}));\n\n// Request logging middleware (skips /health and OPTIONS)\napp.use(\"*\", async (c, next) => { /* timing + debug logging */ });\n```\n\n**Route Registration Pattern**:\n- Routes are registered via `app.route()` and `app.use()` to attach middleware\n- Auth routes mounted at `/auth` with lighter rate limiting (no JWT)\n- Fairness routes (`/fairness/*`) have both JWT middleware AND rate limiting applied\n- Health routes mounted at `/health`\n- Middleware is applied in order to specific path prefixes\n\n**Path Structure**:\n- `/auth/*` → Auth routes (challenge, verify, refresh, logout)\n- `/fairness/coinflip/*` → Coinflip routes\n- `/fairness/lord/*` → Lord of RNGs routes\n- `/closecall/*` → Close Call routes (different structure, not under /fairness)\n- `/fairness/rounds/*` → Round verification/history routes\n- `/health` → Health check\n\n---\n\n### 2. **JWT Auth Middleware** (`src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts`)\n\n**How it works**:\n- Uses `jose` library for HS256 JWT verification\n- Verifies only on **POST requests** — GET requests pass through unauthenticated\n- Extracts JWT from `Authorization: Bearer <token>` header\n- Stores wallet address in context: `c.set(\"wallet\", payload.sub)`\n- Returns 401 for missing/invalid tokens\n\n**Key Points**:\n```typescript\n// JWT claim structure\npayload.sub === wallet address (base58 public key string)\n\n// Validation\n- Algorithm: HS256\n- Claim required: \"sub\" (must be string)\n- Returns: 401 on failure, 403 if JWT wallet doesn't match body wallet\n```\n\n**Applied Routes**:\n```typescript\napp.use(\"/fairness/*\", createJwtAuthMiddleware({ jwtSecret }));\n// All POST requests under /fairness/* require a valid JWT\n```\n\n---\n\n### 3. **Route Handler Pattern** (`src/routes/create.ts` and `src/routes/lord-create.ts`)\n\n**Function Signature**:\n```typescript\nexport function createCoinflipRoutes(deps: CreateRoutesDeps) {\n  const { db, connection, serverKeypair, pdaWatcher } = deps;\n  const app = new Hono<AppEnv>();\n  \n  app.post(\"/create\", async (c) => {\n    // Handler code\n  });\n  \n  return app;\n}\n```\n\n**Dependencies Passed In**:\n- `db: Db` — database client\n- `connection: Connection` — Solana RPC connection\n- `serverKeypair: Keypair` — backend signing key\n- `pdaWatcher?: PdaWatcher` — optional WebSocket watcher for instant join detection\n\n**Hono Context Type**: `Hono<AppEnv>` where `AppEnv` defines `Variables: { wallet: string }`\n\n**Accessing Authenticated Wallet**:\n```typescript\nconst jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n// This is automatically set by JWT middleware for POST requests\n// For defense-in-depth, verify body.wallet matches jwtWallet\n```\n\n**Request/Response Pattern**:\n```typescript\n// Parse request\nconst raw = await c.req.json();\nconst body = validateBody(raw); // Custom validation function\n\n// Return JSON response\nreturn c.json({ key: value }, statusCode);\n\n// Error responses\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 400); // Bad request\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 401); // Unauthorized\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 403); // Forbidden\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 409); // Conflict\nreturn c.json({ error: \"message\" }, 500); // Server error\n```\n\n---\n\n### 4. **Database Patterns** (`src/db.ts`)\n\n**Interface Structure**:\n```typescript\nexport interface Db {\n  insertRound(params: InsertRoundParams): Promise<Round>;\n  getRoundByPda(pda: string): Promise<Round | undefined>;\n  getRoundsByPhase(phase: RoundPhase): Promise<Round[]>;\n  insertUserTransaction(params: InsertUserTransactionParams): Promise<void>;\n  getUserTransactions(wallet: string, cursor?: string, limit?: number, game?: string): Promise<UserTransaction[]>;\n  insertOperatorEvent(pda: string | null, eventType: OperatorEventType, payload?: unknown): Promise<OperatorEvent>;\n  // ... more methods\n}\n```\n\n**getUserTransactions Signature**:\n```typescript\nasync getUserTransactions(\n  wallet: string,\n  cursor?: string,    // Pagination cursor (id of last item)\n  limit?: number,     // Default 20, max 50\n  game?: string       // Optional game filter: \"coinflip\", \"lord\", \"closecall\"\n): Promise<UserTransaction[]>\n\n// Returns array of:\nexport interface UserTransaction {\n  id: string;\n  wallet: string;\n  game: string;\n  match_id: string;\n  event: \"join\" | \"win\" | \"loss\" | \"refund\";\n  amount_lamports: number;\n  tx_sig: string | null;\n  created_at: Date;\n}\n```\n\n**Key Features**:\n- `insertUserTransaction` uses `ON CONFLICT DO NOTHING` for idempotency\n- All amounts are stored in lamports (integers)\n- Database normalizes numeric types (number) on read\n- `cursor` is the `id` field for pagination (lexicographic ordering)\n\n---\n\n### 5. **Common Route Handler Flow** (from `create.ts`)\n\n1. **Parse & Validate Request Body**\n   ```typescript\n   const raw = await c.req.json();\n   const body = validateBody(raw); // throws on invalid data\n   // Catch in try-catch, return 400 with error message\n   ```\n\n2. **Verify JWT Wallet Matches** (defense-in-depth)\n   ```typescript\n   const jwtWallet = c.get(\"wallet\") as string | undefined;\n   if (jwtWallet && body.wallet !== jwtWallet) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Wallet does not match authenticated session\" }, 403);\n   }\n   ```\n\n3. **Convert strings to PublicKey**\n   ```typescript\n   let creatorPubkey: PublicKey;\n   try {\n     creatorPubkey = new PublicKey(body.wallet);\n   } catch {\n     return c.json({ error: \"wallet is not a valid public key\" }, 400);\n   }\n   ```\n\n4. **Generate Game-Specific Data** (secrets, commitments, match IDs)\n   ```typescript\n   const secret = generateSecret(); // cryptographic random\n   const commitment = computeCommitment(secret); // SHA256 hash\n   const matchId = generateMatchId(); // 8-byte random buffer\n   ```\n\n5. **Derive PDA & Check for Duplicates**\n   ```typescript\n   const [matchPda] = deriveMatchPda(creatorPubkey, matchId);\n   const matchPdaStr = matchPda.toBase58();\n   const existing = await db.getRoundByPda(matchPdaStr);\n   if (existing) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Match ID collision — please retry\" }, 409);\n   }\n   ```\n\n6. **Build & Sign Transaction**\n   ```typescript\n   try {\n     const result = await buildCreateMatchTx({ /* params */ });\n     transaction = result.transaction; // serialized, partial-signed\n     lastValidBlockHeight = result.lastValidBlockHeight;\n   } catch (err) {\n     return c.json({ error: \"Failed to build transaction\" }, 500);\n   }\n   ```\n\n7. **Store in Database**\n   ```typescript\n   await db.insertRound({\n     pda: matchPdaStr,\n     game: \"coinflip\",\n     creator: body.wallet,\n     serverKey: serverKeypair.publicKey.toBase58(),\n     secret,\n     commitment,\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n     side: body.side,\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n     phase: \"created\",\n   });\n   ```\n\n8. **Insert User Transaction & Operator Events**\n   ```typescript\n   await db.insertUserTransaction({\n     wallet: body.wallet,\n     game: \"coinflip\",\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n     event: \"join\",\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n   });\n\n   await db.insertOperatorEvent(matchPdaStr, \"secret_generated\", {\n     creator: body.wallet,\n     amountLamports: body.amountLamports,\n     side: body.side,\n     matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n   });\n   ```\n\n9. **Subscribe to PDA Watcher** (for instant join detection)\n   ```typescript\n   pdaWatcher?.watch(matchPdaStr);\n   ```\n\n10. **Return Response**\n    ```typescript\n    return c.json({\n      transaction,        // serialized txn string\n      matchPda: matchPdaStr,\n      matchId: matchId.toString(\"hex\"),\n      commitment: commitment.toString(\"hex\"),\n      lastValidBlockHeight,\n    });\n    ```\n\n---\n\n### 6. **Hono Context Type Definition** (`src/hono-env.ts`)\n\n```typescript\nexport type AppEnv = {\n  Variables: {\n    wallet: string;  // Set by JWT middleware\n  };\n};\n```\n\nAll route handlers should use `Hono<AppEnv>` to get proper type hints for `c.get(\"wallet\")`.\n\n---\n\n### 7. **File Paths & Organization**\n\n| Path | Purpose |\n|------|---------|\n| `src/index.ts` | App setup, middleware registration, route mounting |\n| `src/middleware/jwt-auth.ts` | JWT Bearer token verification |\n| `src/middleware/rate-limit.ts` | Per-wallet and global rate limiting |\n| `src/routes/*.ts` | Individual route handlers (exported as functions) |\n| `src/db.ts` | Database client factory + typed queries |\n| `src/hono-env.ts` | TypeScript context type augmentation |\n| `src/logger.js` | Structured logging (used for audit trails) |\n| `src/tx-builder.ts` | Transaction building utilities |\n| `src/fairness.js` | Commitment/secret generation |\n\n---\n\n### **Key Conventions for New Routes**\n\n1. **Export a factory function** that takes dependencies and returns a `Hono<AppEnv>` app\n2. **Use`app.post()` for operations that modify state** (game creation, joining, settlement)\n3. **Use `app.get()` for read-only queries** (round history, fairness data)\n4. **GET requests skip JWT auth automatically** — only POST requires Bearer token\n5. **Always validate request bodies** with a `validateBody()` function\n6. **Defense-in-depth**: verify `c.get(\"wallet\")` matches request body wallet\n7. **Use `c.json()` for all responses** — Hono handles serialization\n8. **Log at key points** (start, validation failure, DB error, success)\n9. **Database operations use sql template literals** with `postgres.js` client\n10. **Return camelCase in JSON responses** (e.g., `matchPda`, `amountLamports`), snake_case in DB\n\n---\n\n### **Routes Directory Files Summary**\n\n| File | Purpose | HTTP Method | Path |\n|------|---------|-------------|------|\n| `auth.ts` | Sign-in flow | POST | `/auth/challenge`, `/auth/verify`, `/auth/refresh`, `/auth/logout` |\n| `create.ts` | Coinflip round creation | POST | `/fairness/coinflip/create` |\n| `lord-create.ts` | Lord of RNGs round creation | POST | `/fairness/lord/create`, GET `/fairness/lord/current` |\n| `closecall.ts` | Close Call (BTC prediction) | POST/GET | `/closecall/...` |\n| `rounds.ts` | Round verification & history | GET | `/fairness/rounds/history`, `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`, `/fairness/rounds/:pda` |\n| `health.ts` | System health | GET | `/health` |\n\nYou now have the complete pattern to write a new route that follows existing conventions exactly!"}],"totalDurationMs":39966,"totalTokens":59191,"totalToolUseCount":10,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1577,"cache_read_input_tokens":54398,"output_tokens":3213,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":1577},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
