{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_011JcW2NoX4zjMabAvUzN42P","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have everything I need. Let me implement the API route.\n\nKey considerations:\n1. The JWT middleware skips GET requests. I need to either:\n   - Modify the middleware to support an \"all methods\" mode\n   - Handle auth inline in the route handler\n\nThe cleanest approach: modify the JWT middleware to accept an optional `allMethods` flag, then apply it to the `/profile/*` path. This keeps auth logic centralized.\n\nActually, let me think about this again. I could also just use the same middleware with a different config. Let me add a `methods` option.\n\nOr... I could just apply the middleware to `/profile/*` and make the profile route a dedicated handler that handles auth internally. \n\nBut that duplicates JWT logic. The simplest solution is to add a `requireAllMethods` boolean to the JWT config—default false, but when true it enforces auth across all HTTP methods instead of just POST. I'll apply a separate middleware instance to `/profile/*` with this flag enabled. It's a one-line change and fully backward compatible.\n\nNow I'll implement this.\n\nImplementing the middleware configuration... Setting up game name mappings between frontend and database formats, then building the profile route handler that retrieves transaction history for authenticated users.\n\nNow I'm extracting and validating the query parameters—parsing the cursor for pagination, clamping the limit between 1 and 50, and mapping the game filter to its database equivalent while rejecting invalid game names.\n\nFetching the transactions from the database and transforming them back to frontend format, then calculating the next cursor for pagination if there are more results to fetch, and returning the paginated response or catching any database errors.\n\nFor the JWT middleware, I'm adding a configuration option to require authentication on all HTTP methods instead of just POST requests, then updating the middleware check to respect that setting.\n\nNow I'm wiring up the profile routes by mounting the JWT middleware on the `/profile` path with the `requireAllMethods` flag enabled, then attaching the profile route handlers to that path.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1269,"cache_read_input_tokens":43973,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1269},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bdcb16e5-995f-4f3d-baa2-b8a7a74d44d2","uuid":"c197556c-435f-4d9f-a9ac-167a7ff890a2"}
